### HYMN CXVII

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_2011701">1</span></span>Drink Soma,
Lord of Bays, and let it cheer thee: Indra, the  
   stone, like a well-guided courser,  
  Directed by the presser's arms hath pressed it.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_2011702">2</span></span>So let the
draught of joy, thy dear companion, by which, O Lord  
   of Bays, thou slayest foemen,  
  Delight thee, Indra, Lord of princely treasures.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_2011703">3</span></span>Mark
closely, Maghavan; the words I utter, this eulogy recited  
   by Vasishtha:  
  Accept the prayers I offer at thy banquet.

